00:05:51.354 --> 00:05:54.120 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: And let's get into
some more technical aspects

00:05:54.120 --> 00:05:58.470 align:middle line:84%
of dreams that have been
broken down via EEG,

00:05:58.470 --> 00:06:00.229 align:middle line:90%
work in laboratories, and such.

00:06:00.229 --> 00:06:01.770 align:middle line:84%
>> BROWN: Yeah,
well, let me explain.

00:06:01.770 --> 00:06:03.436 align:middle line:84%
I think probably the
most exciting thing

00:06:03.436 --> 00:06:07.560 align:middle line:84%
to really explain is how lucid
dreaming became a science.

00:06:07.560 --> 00:06:10.350 align:middle line:84%
Sleep researchers had,
for the longest time,

00:06:10.350 --> 00:06:13.950 align:middle line:84%
basically pooh-poohed the
whole idea of lucid dreaming.

00:06:13.950 --> 00:06:16.390 align:middle line:84%
It was basically occultists
and spiritual people that

00:06:16.390 --> 00:06:18.780 align:middle line:84%
were talking about it, and
it wasn't really considered

00:06:18.780 --> 00:06:22.170 align:middle line:84%
something that was a
real scientific reality.

00:06:22.170 --> 00:06:26.820 align:middle line:84%
It was through experiments using
EEG monitors and the ability

00:06:26.820 --> 00:06:29.220 align:middle line:84%
to communicate from
within the dream state

00:06:29.220 --> 00:06:31.440 align:middle line:84%
that people were able to
show that lucid dreaming was

00:06:31.440 --> 00:06:33.040 align:middle line:90%
an actual reality.

00:06:33.040 --> 00:06:35.550 align:middle line:84%
So what they would do is they
would hook people up in sleep

00:06:35.550 --> 00:06:39.750 align:middle line:84%
labs while they were sleeping to
EEG monitors so that they could

00:06:39.750 --> 00:06:42.930 align:middle line:84%
demonstrate that the people
were actually in a sleep state--

00:06:42.930 --> 00:06:44.790 align:middle line:84%
whether their
alpha, beta, theta,

00:06:44.790 --> 00:06:46.560 align:middle line:90%
delta states had gone down--

00:06:46.560 --> 00:06:48.810 align:middle line:84%
and that they were
genuinely dreaming.

00:06:48.810 --> 00:06:50.940 align:middle line:84%
And they would
then show that they

00:06:50.940 --> 00:06:53.520 align:middle line:84%
were in what was called REM
sleep-- the rapid eye movement

00:06:53.520 --> 00:06:56.000 align:middle line:84%
stage of sleep where people
are usually most actively

00:06:56.000 --> 00:06:58.500 align:middle line:84%
dreaming-- although they can
dream in other phases of sleep,

00:06:58.500 --> 00:06:59.460 align:middle line:90%
as well.

00:06:59.460 --> 00:07:03.690 align:middle line:84%
But what was remarkable
about this research that--

00:07:03.690 --> 00:07:05.940 align:middle line:84%
Keith Hearne in England
did the first one,

00:07:05.940 --> 00:07:08.680 align:middle line:84%
and the second one was done
by Stephen LaBerge, who

00:07:08.680 --> 00:07:11.380 align:middle line:84%
is a physiologist at
Stanford University.

00:07:11.380 --> 00:07:13.020 align:middle line:84%
And what they
showed, remarkably,

00:07:13.020 --> 00:07:15.240 align:middle line:84%
was that when people
were in the dream state,

00:07:15.240 --> 00:07:18.790 align:middle line:84%
they were able to communicate
by moving their eyes.

00:07:18.790 --> 00:07:20.790 align:middle line:84%
Your eyes are the
one part of your body

00:07:20.790 --> 00:07:24.190 align:middle line:84%
that corresponds from your dream
eyes to your physical body.

00:07:24.190 --> 00:07:26.490 align:middle line:84%
So if you move your
eyes in the dream state,

00:07:26.490 --> 00:07:27.780 align:middle line:90%
they will correspond.

00:07:27.780 --> 00:07:30.360 align:middle line:84%
So here we have the record
from the EEG monitor

00:07:30.360 --> 00:07:32.419 align:middle line:84%
showing the person's
in sleep state,

00:07:32.419 --> 00:07:34.710 align:middle line:84%
and then there are these
sweeping movements of the eyes

00:07:34.710 --> 00:07:37.830 align:middle line:90%
right, left, right, left--

00:07:37.830 --> 00:07:39.340 align:middle line:90%
going back and forth.

00:07:39.340 --> 00:07:41.550 align:middle line:84%
And this was a predetermined,
prearranged code,

00:07:41.550 --> 00:07:43.050 align:middle line:90%
almost like a Morse code.

00:07:43.050 --> 00:07:45.075 align:middle line:84%
So this was really
definitive evidence--

00:07:45.075 --> 00:07:47.760 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: But this was
conscious signaling from

00:07:47.760 --> 00:07:49.840 align:middle line:84%
the lucid dream state
world to the lab techs?

00:07:49.840 --> 00:07:50.640 align:middle line:90%
>> BROWN: Yes.

00:07:50.640 --> 00:07:52.410 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: Yes, that's what
I found really fascinating.

00:07:52.410 --> 00:07:53.210 align:middle line:90%
>> BROWN: Yes, yes.

00:07:53.210 --> 00:07:56.010 align:middle line:84%
And that was what demonstrated
that lucid dreaming was

00:07:56.010 --> 00:07:58.830 align:middle line:84%
a reality, because they
showed that when people were

00:07:58.830 --> 00:08:02.700 align:middle line:84%
in a dream state, they
were able to follow through

00:08:02.700 --> 00:08:05.130 align:middle line:84%
with predetermined
instructions and carry them

00:08:05.130 --> 00:08:07.480 align:middle line:84%
out the procedure, and then
consciously communicate

00:08:07.480 --> 00:08:08.280 align:middle line:90%
from that state.

00:08:08.280 --> 00:08:10.495 align:middle line:84%
Because like I said, they
had just criticized this

00:08:10.495 --> 00:08:12.120 align:middle line:84%
and said they were
skeptical and didn't

00:08:12.120 --> 00:08:13.530 align:middle line:90%
believe it was really true.

00:08:13.530 --> 00:08:16.290 align:middle line:84%
And it's now been
replicated many times

00:08:16.290 --> 00:08:17.930 align:middle line:90%
and many people have done it.

00:08:17.930 --> 00:08:20.490 align:middle line:84%
And they're doing more and more
different types of research

00:08:20.490 --> 00:08:23.510 align:middle line:84%
into locating the area of the
brain that's most responsible.

00:08:23.510 --> 00:08:25.860 align:middle line:84%
Some of the most interesting
neuroscience research

00:08:25.860 --> 00:08:26.930 align:middle line:84%
that's going on
with lucid dreaming

00:08:26.930 --> 00:08:29.550 align:middle line:84%
is they've actually discovered
what's going on in the brain.

00:08:29.550 --> 00:08:31.133 align:middle line:84%
And it's basically
the activation

00:08:31.133 --> 00:08:32.799 align:middle line:84%
of what's called the
prefrontal cortex--

00:08:32.799 --> 00:08:34.380 align:middle line:84%
this area of the
brain right here--

00:08:34.380 --> 00:08:36.900 align:middle line:84%
is normally inactivated
when people are asleep.

00:08:36.900 --> 00:08:39.129 align:middle line:84%
But in a lucid
dream, it becomes--

00:08:39.129 --> 00:08:39.929 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Engaged.

00:08:39.929 --> 00:08:41.137 align:middle line:90%
>> BROWN: It becomes engaged.

00:08:41.137 --> 00:08:43.559 align:middle line:84%
And they've been able to,
with now transcranial brain

00:08:43.559 --> 00:08:47.280 align:middle line:84%
stimulation, actually
activate that in people.

00:08:47.280 --> 00:08:49.880 align:middle line:84%
So on-demand, we can now
have people have lucid dreams

00:08:49.880 --> 00:08:51.880 align:middle line:84%
while they're sleeping
just by activating there.

