that they will fall into
a similar type of pattern

00:17:09.710 --> 00:17:11.960 align:middle line:84%
where they sleep
for about six hours,

00:17:11.960 --> 00:17:14.930 align:middle line:84%
wake up for about two
hours, and then go back

00:17:14.930 --> 00:17:16.550 align:middle line:90%
to sleep for another two hours.

00:17:16.550 --> 00:17:20.300 align:middle line:84%
And what we've lost as a result
of not having those two periods

00:17:20.300 --> 00:17:23.020 align:middle line:84%
of sleep anymore is
that in-between period--

00:17:23.020 --> 00:17:24.770 align:middle line:84%
that period between
first and second

00:17:24.770 --> 00:17:28.220 align:middle line:84%
sleep when people were
not quite fully awake, not

00:17:28.220 --> 00:17:29.330 align:middle line:90%
quite fully asleep.

00:17:29.330 --> 00:17:31.310 align:middle line:84%
I mean, something
similar to hypnogogia,

00:17:31.310 --> 00:17:35.150 align:middle line:84%
but it's described as being a
trance-like, meditative state

00:17:35.150 --> 00:17:37.430 align:middle line:84%
where people would talk
about their dreams,

00:17:37.430 --> 00:17:41.090 align:middle line:84%
maybe walk around a little bit
or converse with their mate

00:17:41.090 --> 00:17:42.480 align:middle line:90%
or something like that.

00:17:42.480 --> 00:17:45.350 align:middle line:84%
And during that period,
I think, it probably

00:17:45.350 --> 00:17:47.870 align:middle line:84%
contributed to greater
periods of lucid dreaming,

00:17:47.870 --> 00:17:49.880 align:middle line:84%
because we know from
lucid dreaming research

00:17:49.880 --> 00:17:52.017 align:middle line:84%
that when people wake
up for a period of time

00:17:52.017 --> 00:17:54.350 align:middle line:84%
in the middle of the night,
get their brain a little bit

00:17:54.350 --> 00:17:55.889 align:middle line:84%
aroused and then
go back to sleep,

00:17:55.889 --> 00:17:58.430 align:middle line:84%
there's a greater chance they're
going to have a lucid dream.

00:17:58.430 --> 00:18:00.320 align:middle line:84%
So I think that that's
one of the things that

00:18:00.320 --> 00:18:01.550 align:middle line:90%
may have gotten lost.

00:18:01.550 --> 00:18:02.440 align:middle line:90%
The other thing is--

00:18:02.440 --> 00:18:05.180 align:middle line:84%
I spoke with Dr.
Rick Strassman, who's

00:18:05.180 --> 00:18:08.150 align:middle line:84%
a researcher at the
University of Mexico.

00:18:08.150 --> 00:18:10.760 align:middle line:84%
As you know, he did amazing,
fascinating research

00:18:10.760 --> 00:18:13.310 align:middle line:90%
with dimethyltryptamine--

00:18:13.310 --> 00:18:15.650 align:middle line:84%
DMT-- which is a
neurotransmitter

00:18:15.650 --> 00:18:16.850 align:middle line:90%
found in the brain.

00:18:16.850 --> 00:18:18.030 align:middle line:90%
It's also a psychedelic.

00:18:18.030 --> 00:18:20.720 align:middle line:84%
It's also used in
the ayahuasca group.

00:18:20.720 --> 00:18:26.030 align:middle line:84%
And he says because all the
exposure to artificial light,

00:18:26.030 --> 00:18:28.280 align:middle line:84%
we're producing less
melatonin in our brain.

00:18:28.280 --> 00:18:30.620 align:middle line:84%
And he thinks as a result,
less DMT production

00:18:30.620 --> 00:18:33.290 align:middle line:84%
in our brain, which then could
affect our dreaming, as well.

00:18:33.290 --> 00:18:34.456 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: That makes sense.

00:18:34.456 --> 00:18:37.220 align:middle line:84%
And it's totally
doable to cure that,

00:18:37.220 --> 00:18:39.710 align:middle line:84%
but you have to
adjust the way you

00:18:39.710 --> 00:18:42.740 align:middle line:84%
want to experience your
world, because I don't

00:18:42.740 --> 00:18:44.720 align:middle line:90%
like artificial light at all.

00:18:44.720 --> 00:18:45.750 align:middle line:90%
I hate it.

00:18:45.750 --> 00:18:48.710 align:middle line:84%
And so in the daytime, I don't
have any lights on in the house

00:18:48.710 --> 00:18:51.970 align:middle line:84%
ever, just windows
open so natural light

00:18:51.970 --> 00:18:54.770 align:middle line:84%
