00:35:10.560 --> 00:35:13.042 align:middle line:84%
your psyche is damaged
from day one, right?

00:35:13.042 --> 00:35:14.000 align:middle line:90%
>> BROWN: Right, right.

00:35:14.000 --> 00:35:16.000 align:middle line:84%
Well, I think that they're
responsible for a lot

00:35:16.000 --> 00:35:18.400 align:middle line:84%
of the anxiety in
waking life, as well.

00:35:18.400 --> 00:35:21.590 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: Absolutely--
and waking life, as well.

00:35:21.590 --> 00:35:22.560 align:middle line:90%
Yeah, we're on that.

00:35:22.560 --> 00:35:24.270 align:middle line:84%
OK, let's talk about
images that people

00:35:24.270 --> 00:35:25.600 align:middle line:90%
see with their eyes closed.

00:35:25.600 --> 00:35:28.550 align:middle line:10%
Let's talk about, now,
moving over into peyote--

00:35:28.550 --> 00:35:30.950 align:middle line:10%
the whole spectrum
of hallucinogens.

00:35:30.950 --> 00:35:33.719 align:middle line:84%
And each one has their
own characteristics.

00:35:33.719 --> 00:35:35.885 align:middle line:84%
>> BROWN: Right, well, when
people do a psychedelic,

00:35:35.885 --> 00:35:38.700 align:middle line:84%
when people do ayahuasca,
peyote, magic mushrooms,

00:35:38.700 --> 00:35:42.020 align:middle line:84%
psilocybin, one of the
most interesting aspects

00:35:42.020 --> 00:35:44.550 align:middle line:84%
of the experience is that
with your eyes closed,

00:35:44.550 --> 00:35:45.680 align:middle line:90%
you tend to see visions.

00:35:45.680 --> 00:35:46.970 align:middle line:90%
You tend to see imagery.

00:35:46.970 --> 00:35:49.370 align:middle line:90%
You tend to see shifting forms.

00:35:49.370 --> 00:35:54.020 align:middle line:84%
You tend to see patterns that
develop into beings or animals

00:35:54.020 --> 00:35:55.910 align:middle line:90%
or scenes or environments.

00:35:55.910 --> 00:35:58.040 align:middle line:84%
And what's most interesting
is that if you really

00:35:58.040 --> 00:36:00.320 align:middle line:84%
pay attention to
this imagery, you

00:36:00.320 --> 00:36:02.600 align:middle line:84%
notice that it's not
completely random, that there's

00:36:02.600 --> 00:36:04.200 align:middle line:90%
some kind of message.

00:36:04.200 --> 00:36:05.990 align:middle line:84%
It's like if you
put them together,

00:36:05.990 --> 00:36:08.000 align:middle line:84%
it's almost like the
different images are

00:36:08.000 --> 00:36:10.250 align:middle line:84%
like different letters
in an alphabet.

00:36:10.250 --> 00:36:12.350 align:middle line:84%
And they're forming
sentences, and it's

00:36:12.350 --> 00:36:14.510 align:middle line:84%
trying to communicate
with you something.

00:36:14.510 --> 00:36:16.310 align:middle line:84%
And in my own
experience with this,

00:36:16.310 --> 00:36:19.610 align:middle line:84%
it really seems like there's
some type of higher mind that

00:36:19.610 --> 00:36:21.230 align:middle line:90%
is using this imagery.

00:36:21.230 --> 00:36:24.380 align:middle line:84%
And the imagery seems very
similar to dream imagery.

00:36:24.380 --> 00:36:28.520 align:middle line:84%
It seems one image can have
four or five different meanings.

00:36:28.520 --> 00:36:32.810 align:middle line:84%
Many meanings are encoded into
a particular image or scene.

00:36:32.810 --> 00:36:35.210 align:middle line:84%
And when you sit there
watching these things--

00:36:35.210 --> 00:36:37.699 align:middle line:84%
particularly on
ayahuasca or mushrooms--

00:36:37.699 --> 00:36:39.740 align:middle line:84%
it's extremely common
where people will sit there

00:36:39.740 --> 00:36:41.600 align:middle line:90%
with their eyes closed.

00:36:41.600 --> 00:36:44.490 align:middle line:84%
First of all, a gap at how
just amazing these things look.

00:36:44.490 --> 00:36:45.290 align:middle line:90%
They're incredible.

00:36:45.290 --> 00:36:46.831 align:middle line:84%
Their visions truly
are-- the colors.

00:36:46.831 --> 00:36:48.360 align:middle line:90%
I mean, they're really amazing.

00:36:48.360 --> 00:36:51.530 align:middle line:84%
But deeper than the bewilderment
from the amazement of that

00:36:51.530 --> 00:36:54.250 align:middle line:84%
is the deep meaning that's
bestowed upon people.

00:36:54.250 --> 00:36:56.000 align:middle line:84%
And if you can really
sit there and really

00:36:56.000 --> 00:36:57.470 align:middle line:84%
watch and really
pay attention, you

00:36:57.470 --> 00:37:00.440 align:middle line:84%
can often learn a
lot about yourself.

00:37:00.440 --> 00:37:03.050 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: And would you say
it's best if you have a guide

00:37:03.050 --> 00:37:05.270 align:middle line:84%
of some kind and you're
taught how to do this,

00:37:05.270 --> 00:37:06.362 align:middle line:90%
or just jump in?

00:37:06.362 --> 00:37:08.320 align:middle line:84%
>> BROWN: Oh, it's always
best to have a guide.

00:37:08.320 --> 00:37:09.819 align:middle line:84%
It's definitely
something that could

00:37:09.819 --> 00:37:13.820 align:middle line:84%
be potentially psychologically
dangerous if someone is not

00:37:13.820 --> 00:37:14.840 align:middle line:90%
properly prepared.

00:37:14.840 --> 00:37:17.990 align:middle line:84%
In indigenous society, it's
always been done with a shaman.

00:37:17.990 --> 00:37:20.480 align:middle line:84%
For thousands of years,
they've always used shamans.

00:37:20.480 --> 00:37:23.210 align:middle line:84%
And right now, of course, what's
going on with psychedelics

00:37:23.210 --> 00:37:25.350 align:middle line:84%
is they're using it
in psychotherapy.

00:37:25.350 --> 00:37:27.260 align:middle line:84%
So it's being used
with a therapist, which

00:37:27.260 --> 00:37:29.887 align:middle line:84%
basically takes the modern
day equivalent of a shaman.

00:37:29.887 --> 00:37:31.970 align:middle line:84%
So these things-- especially
if they're being used

00:37:31.970 --> 00:37:32.870 align:middle line:90%
for healing--

00:37:32.870 --> 00:37:34.760 align:middle line:84%
are almost always
far more effective

00:37:34.760 --> 00:37:37.250 align:middle line:84%
if they're used in conjunction
with some other healing

00:37:37.250 --> 00:37:38.050 align:middle line:90%
modality.

00:37:38.050 --> 00:37:40.299 align:middle line:84%
They work very well,
synergistically, on their own.

00:37:40.299 --> 00:37:41.840 align:middle line:84%
They're not quite
nearly as powerful,

00:37:41.840 --> 00:37:43.760 align:middle line:84%
and they can be a
lot more dangerous.

00:37:43.760 --> 00:37:46.040 align:middle line:84%
But together, they
really can be powerful.

00:37:46.040 --> 00:37:48.860 align:middle line:84%
And together, they're
usually pretty safe.

00:37:48.860 --> 00:37:52.130 align:middle line:84%
And people have really had
some really amazing healing

00:37:52.130 --> 00:37:53.570 align:middle line:90%
experiences with ayahuasca.

00:37:53.570 --> 00:37:56.360 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: Yeah, we hear about
all the people that have done

00:37:56.360 --> 00:37:58.070 align:middle line:90%
LSD forever.

00:37:58.070 --> 00:38:00.710 align:middle line:84%
And again, just under
their own steam.

00:38:00.710 --> 00:38:02.600 align:middle line:84%
And that's a whole
different thing.

00:38:02.600 --> 00:38:07.880 align:middle line:84%
I mean, you do have to be
somewhat careful about your use

00:38:07.880 --> 00:38:09.220 align:middle line:90%
of hallucinogens.

00:38:09.220 --> 00:38:12.382 align:middle line:84%
I mean, I'm one of those people
that tries everything once.

00:38:12.382 --> 00:38:14.090 align:middle line:84%
Not everything, but
a lot of things once,

00:38:14.090 --> 00:38:15.214 align:middle line:90%
just to see what it's like.

00:38:15.214 --> 00:38:19.950 align:middle line:90%
And wow-- just randomly.

00:38:19.950 --> 00:38:21.660 align:middle line:90%
No education first.

00:38:21.660 --> 00:38:22.460 align:middle line:90%
No guidance.

00:38:22.460 --> 00:38:24.980 align:middle line:84%
Just like, hm, I wonder
what that would feel like?

00:38:24.980 --> 00:38:27.640 align:middle line:84%
And so I've had the
experiences that way.

00:38:27.640 --> 00:38:29.210 align:middle line:90%
And it's been interesting.

00:38:29.210 --> 00:38:31.490 align:middle line:84%
I mean, going to the
Louvre on LSD was fine.

00:38:31.490 --> 00:38:33.186 align:middle line:84%
I mean, I got stuck
looking at those--

00:38:33.186 --> 00:38:34.602 align:middle line:84%
can't remember the
artist's name--

00:38:34.602 --> 00:38:37.270 align:middle line:84%
those fruit and vegetable
heads from the 1500s.

00:38:37.270 --> 00:38:37.820 align:middle line:84%
>> BROWN: I know
who you're talking--

00:38:37.820 --> 00:38:40.278 align:middle line:84%
I can't remember the artist,
but I know who you mean, yeah.

00:38:40.278 --> 00:38:42.290 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: I stayed there
almost the whole time,

00:38:42.290 --> 00:38:44.960 align:middle line:84%
and then ended up out on
a ledge on the third floor

00:38:44.960 --> 00:38:46.310 align:middle line:90%
of the cafeteria--

00:38:46.310 --> 00:38:50.900 align:middle line:84%
sitting on a ledge having
a snack with pigeons.

00:38:50.900 --> 00:38:52.212 align:middle line:90%
So it had its ups and downs.

00:38:52.212 --> 00:38:53.420 align:middle line:90%
>> BROWN: So you and I, both.

00:38:53.420 --> 00:38:54.890 align:middle line:90%
I walked around Paris--

00:38:54.890 --> 00:38:56.120 align:middle line:90%
when I was in college I did.

00:38:56.120 --> 00:38:58.130 align:middle line:84%
I went to the Pompidou Center
while tripping on acid.

00:38:58.130 --> 00:38:58.930 align:middle line:90%
It was so fun.

00:38:58.930 --> 00:39:00.500 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: It really was fun.

00:39:00.500 --> 00:39:03.066 align:middle line:84%
They just asked us to
get back off of the ledge

00:39:03.066 --> 00:39:04.190 align:middle line:90%
