00:39:06.862 --> 00:39:10.430 align:middle line:84%
I mean, everyone has
their unique experience.

00:39:10.430 --> 00:39:12.260 align:middle line:84%
And it also depends
a lot, though,

00:39:12.260 --> 00:39:14.960 align:middle line:84%
on the psychology
that's underneath it

00:39:14.960 --> 00:39:18.320 align:middle line:84%
and your own base,
psychologically,

00:39:18.320 --> 00:39:21.890 align:middle line:84%
at the time-- whether it's
stable, unstable, more aware

00:39:21.890 --> 00:39:24.470 align:middle line:90%
or more depressed, for example.

00:39:24.470 --> 00:39:28.237 align:middle line:84%
So what do you have to say
along that line about what

00:39:28.237 --> 00:39:30.320 align:middle line:84%
you would encourage people
to do if they're really

00:39:30.320 --> 00:39:32.420 align:middle line:84%
looking for themselves
and having a hard time--

00:39:32.420 --> 00:39:33.520 align:middle line:90%
depressed, say, even?

00:39:33.520 --> 00:39:35.270 align:middle line:84%
>> BROWN: With
psychedelics, you mean, or?

00:39:35.270 --> 00:39:36.267 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Yeah.

00:39:36.267 --> 00:39:38.600 align:middle line:84%
>> BROWN: The most important
thing to remember about any

00:39:38.600 --> 00:39:40.310 align:middle line:84%
psychedelic experience--
well, first of all,

00:39:40.310 --> 00:39:41.934 align:middle line:84%
is reading as much
about it as you can.

00:39:41.934 --> 00:39:44.109 align:middle line:84%
Educate yourself is the
most important thing.

00:39:44.109 --> 00:39:46.400 align:middle line:84%
The next thing I would say
that's really most important

00:39:46.400 --> 00:39:48.800 align:middle line:84%
is understanding
set and setting.

00:39:48.800 --> 00:39:52.190 align:middle line:84%
Your set is the mental
state that you're

00:39:52.190 --> 00:39:53.930 align:middle line:84%
in-- whether you're
depressed, happy.

00:39:53.930 --> 00:39:55.640 align:middle line:84%
You obviously want
to be in a state

00:39:55.640 --> 00:39:58.070 align:middle line:84%
where you're feeling
very emotionally stable.

00:39:58.070 --> 00:40:00.170 align:middle line:84%
The setting is the
place where you actually

00:40:00.170 --> 00:40:01.467 align:middle line:90%
do it-- your environment.

00:40:01.467 --> 00:40:03.800 align:middle line:84%
You want to be in a place
where you feel very safe, very

00:40:03.800 --> 00:40:06.350 align:middle line:84%
comfortable, where there's no
interruptions, where you're

00:40:06.350 --> 00:40:09.170 align:middle line:84%
with people that you don't
feel any kind of animosity

00:40:09.170 --> 00:40:11.790 align:middle line:84%
with, where you feel
close bonding with.

00:40:11.790 --> 00:40:15.650 align:middle line:84%
Because I mean, doing this with
someone is extremely intimate.

00:40:15.650 --> 00:40:17.630 align:middle line:84%
It's like becoming
naked with someone.

00:40:17.630 --> 00:40:19.620 align:middle line:84%
You become like a
little baby again.

00:40:19.620 --> 00:40:21.980 align:middle line:84%
So it's a very, very,
very powerful experience

00:40:21.980 --> 00:40:24.660 align:middle line:84%
that can go off in all
different directions.

00:40:24.660 --> 00:40:26.479 align:middle line:84%
So it's very important
to be with someone

00:40:26.479 --> 00:40:28.020 align:middle line:84%
who knows what
they're doing, really,

00:40:28.020 --> 00:40:31.022 align:middle line:84%
and to work with
somebody who's actually

00:40:31.022 --> 00:40:33.480 align:middle line:84%
had the experience before you--
to talk to other people who

00:40:33.480 --> 00:40:34.520 align:middle line:90%
have had the experience.

00:40:34.520 --> 00:40:37.450 align:middle line:90%


00:40:37.450 --> 00:40:39.300 align:middle line:84%
And preferably to
be with someone

00:40:39.300 --> 00:40:41.861 align:middle line:84%
who's had the experience
when you do it.

00:40:41.861 --> 00:40:43.860 align:middle line:84%
The word they don't really
use anymore is guide.

00:40:43.860 --> 00:40:45.030 align:middle line:90%
They've stopped using that.

00:40:45.030 --> 00:40:46.196 align:middle line:90%
The maps stopped using that.

00:40:46.196 --> 00:40:47.820 align:middle line:84%
The word they use
now is "sitter,"

00:40:47.820 --> 00:40:48.330 align:middle line:90%
because you don't want to--

00:40:48.330 --> 00:40:49.130 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Sitter.

00:40:49.130 --> 00:40:50.790 align:middle line:84%
Sitter is like a
babysitter, right.

00:40:50.790 --> 00:40:52.120 align:middle line:84%
>> BROWN: Because you don't
want to influence, so much,

00:40:52.120 --> 00:40:54.703 align:middle line:84%
their experiences, just be there
with them to be there if they

00:40:54.703 --> 00:40:56.444 align:middle line:90%
need you.

00:40:56.444 --> 00:40:58.860 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: Now, some of the
experiences people have during

00:40:58.860 --> 00:41:01.680 align:middle line:84%
sleep and will try to relate
these back and forth during

00:41:01.680 --> 00:41:04.320 align:middle line:84%
sleep-- and also,
I think, at times,

00:41:04.320 --> 00:41:06.360 align:middle line:84%
when they're using
various hallucinogens--

00:41:06.360 --> 00:41:09.200 align:middle line:90%
is a state of paralysis.

00:41:09.200 --> 00:41:10.920 align:middle line:84%
Can you talk about
that a little bit?

00:41:10.920 --> 00:41:12.780 align:middle line:84%
>> BROWN: Yeah, well,
sleep paralysis.

00:41:12.780 --> 00:41:16.020 align:middle line:84%
Sleep paralysis is a state
when people sometimes

00:41:16.020 --> 00:41:17.850 align:middle line:84%
experience when they
wake up in the morning

00:41:17.850 --> 00:41:19.650 align:middle line:84%
and they're not
fully woken up yet

00:41:19.650 --> 00:41:21.150 align:middle line:90%
and they can't move their body.

00:41:21.150 --> 00:41:25.760 align:middle line:84%
And it's often a terrifying
experience for people.

00:41:25.760 --> 00:41:27.835 align:middle line:84%
They're unable to
move, and they often

00:41:27.835 --> 00:41:30.210 align:middle line:84%
struggle, struggle, struggle
really, really, really hard.

00:41:30.210 --> 00:41:32.220 align:middle line:84%
And in that interim,
trying to move,

00:41:32.220 --> 00:41:34.864 align:middle line:84%
they're still in
somewhat REM sleep.

00:41:34.864 --> 00:41:36.780 align:middle line:84%
So they're actually
seeing some dream imagery,

00:41:36.780 --> 00:41:39.180 align:middle line:84%
and it's very common for
them to experience, say,

00:41:39.180 --> 00:41:42.430 align:middle line:84%
a menacing figure to be coming
towards them or something.

00:41:42.430 --> 00:41:44.790 align:middle line:84%
And people get very frightened
and often just startle

00:41:44.790 --> 00:41:47.760 align:middle line:90%
and jump awake very quickly.

00:41:47.760 --> 00:41:50.850 align:middle line:84%
That state of sleep
paralysis, I've learned,

00:41:50.850 --> 00:41:53.250 align:middle line:84%
is actually a launching
pad for lucid dreaming

00:41:53.250 --> 00:41:54.805 align:middle line:90%
if you learn to not--

00:41:54.805 --> 00:41:55.680 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Freak out.

00:41:55.680 --> 00:41:58.054 align:middle line:84%
>> BROWN: Yeah, if you learn
to not freak out and get too

00:41:58.054 --> 00:42:02.220 align:middle line:84%
scared and just stay there with
it and focus your attention

00:42:02.220 --> 00:42:05.640 align:middle line:84%
from your physical body to--
if you try to move your body,

00:42:05.640 --> 00:42:09.226 align:middle line:84%
you realize your body doesn't
move, but something does.

00:42:09.226 --> 00:42:11.100 align:middle line:84%
There's like an astral
limb, or a dream limb,

00:42:11.100 --> 00:42:12.270 align:middle line:90%
or something that moves.

00:42:12.270 --> 00:42:16.620 align:middle line:84%
And if you start trying to focus
your attention on that instead

00:42:16.620 --> 00:42:18.390 align:middle line:84%
of your physical
body, you'll slowly

00:42:18.390 --> 00:42:22.634 align:middle line:84%
start to identify more with the
dream body or the astral body.

00:42:22.634 --> 00:42:24.300 align:middle line:84%
And you can then use
that as a launching

00:42:24.300 --> 00:42:26.190 align:middle line:84%
pad to go off into an
out-of-body experience

00:42:26.190 --> 00:42:27.480 align:middle line:90%
or lucid dream.

00:42:27.480 --> 00:42:30.270 align:middle line:84%
So that's one of the
techniques that I've actually

00:42:30.270 --> 00:42:32.110 align:middle line:90%
learned from sleep paralysis.

00:42:32.110 --> 00:42:34.350 align:middle line:84%
The reason that people
go into sleep paralysis

00:42:34.350 --> 00:42:38.820 align:middle line:84%
is because when
people are sleeping,

00:42:38.820 --> 00:42:41.640 align:middle line:84%
it's probably not
advantageous for their bodies

00:42:41.640 --> 00:42:44.369 align:middle line:84%
to be moving around and
acting out the dreams--

00:42:44.369 --> 00:42:45.410 align:middle line:90%
the actions of the dream.

00:42:45.410 --> 00:42:47.700 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: Well, especially
if you're what's called astral

00:42:47.700 --> 00:42:48.510 align:middle line:90%
traveling.

00:42:48.510 --> 00:42:51.760 align:middle line:84%
You want the body to be
quiet and safe, right?

00:42:51.760 --> 00:42:54.240 align:middle line:84%
And there's a fine
line between dreaming

00:42:54.240 --> 00:42:55.920 align:middle line:90%
and what we call astral travel.

00:42:55.920 --> 00:42:58.510 align:middle line:90%
It can look very similar.

00:42:58.510 --> 00:43:01.260 align:middle line:84%
>> BROWN: Well, the big
difference between dreaming

00:43:01.260 --> 00:43:03.700 align:middle line:84%
and astral traveling is that
we can very clearly define

00:43:03.700 --> 00:43:04.500 align:middle line:90%
dreaming.

00:43:04.500 --> 00:43:06.000 align:middle line:84%
Astral traveling's
hard to define,

