Ask it, say, what
do you represent?

00:51:34.250 --> 00:51:35.320 align:middle line:90%
What are you here?

00:51:35.320 --> 00:51:36.260 align:middle line:84%
Try to hug the
creature if you can.

00:51:36.260 --> 00:51:37.390 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: Yes, that's
very good advice.

00:51:37.390 --> 00:51:40.040 align:middle line:84%
>> BROWN: Yeah, and then you
can actually help to integrate

00:51:40.040 --> 00:51:44.240 align:middle line:84%
and process those repressed or
damaged emotions and traumas

00:51:44.240 --> 00:51:45.147 align:middle line:90%
and things like that.

00:51:45.147 --> 00:51:47.480 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: And sometimes
you're actually helping to heal

00:51:47.480 --> 00:51:48.890 align:middle line:90%
another entity.

00:51:48.890 --> 00:51:50.490 align:middle line:90%
>> BROWN: Exactly, right, yeah.

00:51:50.490 --> 00:51:52.620 align:middle line:84%
So you're helping
each other, then.

00:51:52.620 --> 00:51:54.370 align:middle line:84%
What a beautiful
experience that could be.

00:51:54.370 --> 00:51:57.260 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: Indeed-- if you're
cognizant enough not to just

00:51:57.260 --> 00:51:58.286 align:middle line:90%
start running.

00:51:58.286 --> 00:52:00.950 align:middle line:90%
Which most people do, of course.

00:52:00.950 --> 00:52:02.090 align:middle line:90%
You know, another area--

00:52:02.090 --> 00:52:04.640 align:middle line:84%
we only have a few minutes left,
but I find it fascinating--

00:52:04.640 --> 00:52:08.420 align:middle line:84%
is the notion of how
magnetic fields work with us.

00:52:08.420 --> 00:52:10.190 align:middle line:84%
We know how they work
with us in daytime.

00:52:10.190 --> 00:52:12.020 align:middle line:84%
I mean, a lot of
people do, anyway--

00:52:12.020 --> 00:52:12.980 align:middle line:90%
our waking mind.

00:52:12.980 --> 00:52:15.760 align:middle line:84%
And we're having a lot
of issues at large.

00:52:15.760 --> 00:52:18.290 align:middle line:84%
People are having
short-term memory loss.

00:52:18.290 --> 00:52:21.380 align:middle line:84%
As the magnetic field of the
Earth continues dissipating,

00:52:21.380 --> 00:52:23.480 align:middle line:84%
we're seeing more
unstable behaviors.

00:52:23.480 --> 00:52:24.920 align:middle line:90%
I mean, that's just a fact.

00:52:24.920 --> 00:52:26.840 align:middle line:84%
And we can't blame
it all on psyops.

00:52:26.840 --> 00:52:29.570 align:middle line:84%
I mean, there is also
the damaging effect.

00:52:29.570 --> 00:52:32.180 align:middle line:84%
Not damaging-- the lack of
support of the magnetic field

00:52:32.180 --> 00:52:33.380 align:middle line:90%
that once was.

00:52:33.380 --> 00:52:35.870 align:middle line:84%
And you talk about the
relationship between dreams

00:52:35.870 --> 00:52:39.270 align:middle line:84%
and the magnetic fields of
Earth in the book, as well.

00:52:39.270 --> 00:52:41.580 align:middle line:84%
>> BROWN: I talk about
the volcanic activity.

00:52:41.580 --> 00:52:42.955 align:middle line:84%
Is that what you're
referring to?

00:52:42.955 --> 00:52:45.530 align:middle line:84%
The volcanic activity in
the Hawaiian Islands--

00:52:45.530 --> 00:52:47.720 align:middle line:84%
I was speaking to
a researcher who

00:52:47.720 --> 00:52:52.220 align:middle line:84%
talked about how there's a
relationship between reports

00:52:52.220 --> 00:52:55.730 align:middle line:84%
of sleep paralysis
and volcanic activity

00:52:55.730 --> 00:52:58.400 align:middle line:90%
in the Hawaiian Islands.

00:52:58.400 --> 00:52:59.980 align:middle line:90%
Now, what that means is really--

00:52:59.980 --> 00:53:00.780 align:middle line:90%
who knows?

00:53:00.780 --> 00:53:02.930 align:middle line:84%
But in part of my research
with Rupert Sheldrake,

00:53:02.930 --> 00:53:06.110 align:middle line:84%
I also learned that
there's a relationship

00:53:06.110 --> 00:53:09.350 align:middle line:84%
between the crystals in the
earth and the Piezoelectric

00:53:09.350 --> 00:53:10.937 align:middle line:90%
effect and animal behavior.

00:53:10.937 --> 00:53:12.770 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: That's all
electromagnetic, yeah.

00:53:12.770 --> 00:53:13.900 align:middle line:84%
>> BROWN: Gives off
electric fields.

00:53:13.900 --> 00:53:15.980 align:middle line:84%
These electric fields
can influence an animal's

00:53:15.980 --> 00:53:18.860 align:middle line:84%
nervous system, influence
their neurotransmitter levels,

00:53:18.860 --> 00:53:21.670 align:middle line:84%
and influence their behavior
in interesting ways.

00:53:21.670 --> 00:53:24.260 align:middle line:84%
So we know that
geologic activity

00:53:24.260 --> 00:53:27.290 align:middle line:84%
can influence nervous
systems, influence behavior.

00:53:27.290 --> 00:53:29.430 align:middle line:84%
And what's going on in
the volcanic islands

00:53:29.430 --> 00:53:30.230 align:middle line:90%
is fascinating.

00:53:30.230 --> 00:53:32.325 align:middle line:84%
People are experiencing
more sleep paralysis

00:53:32.325 --> 00:53:33.200 align:middle line:90%
during these periods.

00:53:33.200 --> 00:53:36.020 align:middle line:84%
So if you want to
time it, you can

00:53:36.020 --> 00:53:38.157 align:middle line:84%
try to have--
sleep paralysis can

00:53:38.157 --> 00:53:39.740 align:middle line:84%
be a launching pad
for lucid dreaming,

00:53:39.740 --> 00:53:40.781 align:middle line:90%
like I mentioned earlier.

00:53:40.781 --> 00:53:42.636 align:middle line:84%
So try to get to the
Hawaiian Islands.

00:53:42.636 --> 00:53:44.010 align:middle line:84%
Hang out where
there's volcanoes.

00:53:44.010 --> 00:53:48.162 align:middle line:84%
But there might be safer ways to
have lucid dreams than hanging

00:53:48.162 --> 00:53:49.400 align:middle line:90%
out on top of a volcano.

00:53:49.400 --> 00:53:50.556 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: I would agree.

00:53:50.556 --> 00:53:52.430 align:middle line:84%
And then I think a lot
of people, the biggest

00:53:52.430 --> 00:53:54.740 align:middle line:84%
frustration-- and this
will be my final question--

00:53:54.740 --> 00:53:57.510 align:middle line:84%
is that you have
a fabulous dream

00:53:57.510 --> 00:53:59.120 align:middle line:90%
and then you don't remember it.

00:53:59.120 --> 00:54:01.460 align:middle line:84%
So what are some
general practices

00:54:01.460 --> 00:54:04.550 align:middle line:84%
you find useful to help
people just simply remember

00:54:04.550 --> 00:54:06.570 align:middle line:84%
all their dreams, just
remember your dreams?

00:54:06.570 --> 00:54:08.330 align:middle line:84%
>> BROWN: Yeah, well, the most
important thing if you really

00:54:08.330 --> 00:54:10.190 align:middle line:84%
want to remember dreams--
which is actually essential

00:54:10.190 --> 00:54:12.560 align:middle line:84%
for becoming lucid in dreams,
is remembering your dreams

00:54:12.560 --> 00:54:13.220 align:middle line:90%
better--

00:54:13.220 --> 00:54:14.860 align:middle line:84%
is to start paying
attention to them.

00:54:14.860 --> 00:54:16.693 align:middle line:84%
That's really just the
most important thing.

00:54:16.693 --> 00:54:18.050 align:middle line:90%
Start writing them down.

00:54:18.050 --> 00:54:19.425 align:middle line:84%
If you have a
snippet of a dream,

00:54:19.425 --> 00:54:21.133 align:middle line:84%
write it down in the
middle of the night.

00:54:21.133 --> 00:54:22.600 align:middle line:84%
Always keep a pad
next to your bed.

00:54:22.600 --> 00:54:24.920 align:middle line:84%
Always keep-- or a audio
recorder, something

00:54:24.920 --> 00:54:26.680 align:middle line:84%
where you can always
write it down.

00:54:26.680 --> 00:54:29.270 align:middle line:84%
Even if you just have a feeling,
write down that feeling.

00:54:29.270 --> 00:54:31.410 align:middle line:90%
I feel a little bit nauseous.

00:54:31.410 --> 00:54:32.600 align:middle line:90%
I feel anxious.

00:54:32.600 --> 00:54:34.290 align:middle line:84%
I feel happy-- whatever
the feeling is.

00:54:34.290 --> 00:54:35.190 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: Keep your
old dream journal there.

00:54:35.190 --> 00:54:37.520 align:middle line:84%
>> BROWN: Yeah, and you find
that the more attention--

00:54:37.520 --> 00:54:38.960 align:middle line:84%
the more you start
writing down--

00:54:38.960 --> 00:54:40.430 align:middle line:90%
more starts coming back to you.

00:54:40.430 --> 00:54:41.570 align:middle line:90%
It starts snowballing.

00:54:41.570 --> 00:54:43.220 align:middle line:84%
You start doing that
for a couple days,

00:54:43.220 --> 00:54:45.011 align:middle line:84%
and you'll actually
start to remember more.

00:54:45.011 --> 00:54:47.210 align:middle line:84%
So keeping a dream
journal, paying attention,

00:54:47.210 --> 00:54:49.490 align:middle line:84%
writing down whatever it
is that you remember--

00:54:49.490 --> 00:54:50.930 align:middle line:90%
even if it's just a feeling--

00:54:50.930 --> 00:54:53.180 align:middle line:84%
and then sometimes
just lying in the dark

00:54:53.180 --> 00:54:55.130 align:middle line:84%
without turning the
light on is a good way

00:54:55.130 --> 00:54:58.414 align:middle line:84%
to help bring back dreams before
they dissolve into the ether.

00:54:58.414 --> 00:54:59.330 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Absolutely.

00:54:59.330 --> 00:55:00.746 align:middle line:84%
Another little
trick I found, too,

00:55:00.746 --> 00:55:05.570 align:middle line:84%
was tell your subconscious mind
that when the crux of the dream

00:55:05.570 --> 00:55:07.970 align:middle line:84%
comes through-- the really
important part, the message--

00:55:07.970 --> 00:55:12.410 align:middle line:84%
to be sure to gently
but surely wake me up.

00:55:12.410 --> 00:55:15.270 align:middle line:84%
Wake me up when the major
message comes through

00:55:15.270 --> 00:55:16.070 align:middle line:90%
so I don't miss it.

00:55:16.070 --> 00:55:18.830 align:middle line:84%
Because otherwise, you're just
going from dream to dream.

00:55:18.830 --> 00:55:19.940 align:middle line:84%
And I found that works
pretty well, too.

00:55:19.940 --> 00:55:22.611 align:middle line:84%
>> BROWN: Yeah, you can instruct
your unconscious just to follow

00:55:22.611 --> 00:55:24.110 align:middle line:84%
through, and it
will follow through.

00:55:24.110 --> 00:55:25.026 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Absolutely.

00:55:25.026 --> 00:55:26.740 align:middle line:84%
Any final thoughts
before we say goodbye?

